attributes.Long form description: The instructor asks the student to disassemble the furniture. The student grabs the Allen wrench and starts with the first eight screws to release the top plate. Then the student uses a tool and her hand to unscrew the screws and rotates the furniture to make it easier to work. The student then sets the screws and the top plate on the table and continues with the other eight remaining screws. Next, the student unscrews the screws in pairs to release the furniture legs and rotates the furniture. The student drops the Allen wrench and one leg during this process. The student completes the disassembly. The instructor asks the student to press stop.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the top shelf.
The student disassembles the first leg.
The student disassembles the second leg.
The student disassembles the third leg.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student removes the hex socket head and drops the table leg.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the fourth leg.

attributes.Transcription: Now you can press the stop.
